#
# Extract literate-markdown blocks from a script. Any line matching the
# pattern `## @md ...` is emitted with the `## @md ` prefix stripped, so a
# script can carry markdown prose interleaved with its code and have the
# prose extracted verbatim. Usage: `mddoc <file>` writes the extracted
# markdown to stdout. Lines without the marker are ignored.

# shellcheck disable=SC1090
grep '^\s*## @md' "$1" | sed -e 's/^\s*## @md\s*//'
